semantic_equivalence_artifact.original_latex_theorem:
[c.f.~\cite{Iliopoulos88,McKenzieC87}] \label{lemma-I88}
From a list $\pi_1, \ldots, \pi_m, \pi \in S_n$ of pairwise commuting permutations one can 
compute in polynomial time the following:
\begin{itemize}
\item unary encoded numbers
$n_1, \ldots, n_d$ such that $\langle \pi_1, \ldots, \pi_m \rangle \cong \prod_{j=1}^d \integers_{n_j}$ and
\item an isomorphism
$h : \langle \pi_1, \ldots, \pi_m \rangle \to \prod_{i=1}^d \integers_{n_i}$ that is represented by $h(\pi_1), \ldots, h(\pi_m)$.
\end{itemize}

